  "chunk_index": 10,
  "summary": "After discovering the strangled body of Elena Marshall, Emily Bruster and Patrick Redfern decide not to touch the scene and wait for the police. To avoid being alone on the beach with a potential killer, Emily rows a boat to Ladekapi Bay to seek help while Patrick remains to guard the body.\n\nAt the scene, Detective Inspector Colgate and Dr. Nisden conduct an examination. Dr. Nisden determines that Elena was strangled by someone with a strong grip and likely caught her off guard. Based on the discovery time of approximately 11:45, Dr. Nisden estimates the time of death occurred between 10:45 and 11:40. Emily identifies the deceased as a guest from the Pirate's Flag Inn.\n\nPolice Commissioner Colonel Weston meets Hercule Poirot at the site. Poirot reveals that he was the last person to see Mrs. Marshall alive; he helped her push a raft into the water around 10:15, after which she paddled alone toward Elfin Bay. Poirot also discloses that Mrs. Marshall had requested he keep their encounter a secret. The investigation considers the possibility of an affair between Mrs. Marshall and Patrick, noting that Patrick may have followed her to the area. Meanwhile, the police question Mrs. Castle, the proprietor of the Black Swan Inn, regarding the nature of the guests at her establishment.",
